==English==
===Pronunciation===
*(''UK''): krō'kā, /ˈkrəʊkeɪ/, /<tt>"kr@UkeI</tt>/
*(''US''): krōkā', /kroʊˈkeɪ/, /<tt>kroU"keI</tt>/

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''croquet''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''croquets''')

#(''uncountable'') A [[game]] played on a [[lawn]], in which players use [[mallet]]s to drive [[wooden]] [[ball]]s through [[hoop]]s ([[wicket]]s)
#(''uncountable'') A [[shot]] in this game in which the [[opponent]]'s ball is driven away by hitting one's own ball when they are in contact
#(''uncountable'') A [[croquette]].

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|croquet||}}

#To use a croquet to drive away an [[opponent]]'s ball.

